Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,你们有没有想过
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is much speculation by some
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.52,0:00:07.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗任务中的计算机是怎么把人类送上月球的?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.52,0:00:07.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,as to how the flight computer aboard the Apollo missions managed to get men to the moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.64,0:00:13.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,在那时计算机运算能力都不如现在的一个智能手机
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.64,0:00:13.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,when it had just a tiny fraction of the computing power of something like a modern smartphone.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.77,0:00:15.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,但首先这里有个误区
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.77,0:00:15.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,But this is quite misleading,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.60,0:00:20.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,并不是一台独立的计算机控制阿波罗飞船 而是四台
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.60,0:00:20.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,as there was not one solitary computer controlling the Apollo craft, there were 4 computers.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.74,0:00:22.68,辉中,,0,0,0,,没有花花绿绿的触摸屏
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.74,0:00:22.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,And no fancy touch screens,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.68,0:00:27.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,没有图形界面 为了节省资源 如今各种计算机有的功能它都没有
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.68,0:00:27.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,GUI’s or other things in a typical computer of today to waste resources on.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.33,0:00:33.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,四台计算机中第一台是运载火箭数字计算机 LVDC
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.33,0:00:33.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first of the 4 computers was the Saturn Launch Vehicle Digital Computer or LVDC.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.25,0:00:37.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,它控制火箭从发射架起飞到近地轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.25,0:00:37.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,This got the rocket from the launch pad to earth orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.11,0:00:41.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后就是阿波罗制导计算机 AGC了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.11,0:00:41.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,Then there was the Apollo Guidance Computer or AGC.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.69,0:00:44.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是绝大多数人比较关注的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.69,0:00:44.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is the one the most people think of.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.65,0:00:46.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,实际上 这当中有两台
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.65,0:00:46.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,There were in fact, two of them.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.68,0:00:50.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,一台在指令舱中 控制阿波罗号从地球飞到月球再飞回来
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.68,0:00:50.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,One in the Command Module to get from the earth orbit to the moon and back again.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.15,0:00:55.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,第二台在登月舱里 控制月球着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.15,0:00:55.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,The second was in the lunar lander that would control the landing,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.29,0:00:58.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,再次起飞和与指令舱对接
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.29,0:00:58.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,and then the ascent back to the command module and docking.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.05,0:01:03.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,最后一台计算机在阿波罗系列任务中从来没用过
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.05,0:01:03.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,The fourth computer was one which was never used on any missions,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.20,0:01:07.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它在月球下降、着陆过程中控制紧急终止并再次起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.20,0:01:07.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,because it would control an emergency abort and ascent,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.40,0:01:10.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它在月球下降、着陆过程中控制紧急终止并再次起飞
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.40,0:01:10.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,should something happen during the descent to the moons surface,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.70,0:01:14.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果在这期间着陆计算机失效或者燃油告急
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.70,0:01:14.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the landing computer failing or they ran out of fuel.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.60,0:01:18.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,AGC并不像当年其他计算机那样特别笨重
Dialogue: 2,0:01:14.60,0:01:18.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Apollo Guidance Computer wasn’t as dumb as many make it out to be.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.88,0:01:21.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,在阿波罗任务研发过程中
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.88,0:01:21.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,As time when by in Apollo’s development,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.24,0:01:25.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,大量有难度的任务源源不断
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.24,0:01:25.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,the tasks that it was meant to do increased in both number and sophistication.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.25,0:01:30.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,由于资源有限，随之带来的问题也越来越多
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.25,0:01:30.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,This in turn created ever more issues with the limited resources available.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.68,0:01:34.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,其中最大的问题就是存储空间不够
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.68,0:01:34.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,One of the biggest problems was the limited amount of memory
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.67,0:01:37.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,鉴于当时技术限制
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.67,0:01:37.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,due to the technological limitations of the time.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.47,0:01:42.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,程序员必须充分利用每一字节的空间
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.47,0:01:42.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,This meant that the programmers had to make use of every single byte available.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.88,0:01:45.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,AGC还有一个独一无二的操作系统
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.88,0:01:45.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,The AGC also had a unique operating system.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.22,0:01:49.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像UNIX、Linux、Windows和iOS一样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.22,0:01:49.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,Systems like UNIX, Linux, Windows and Apple iOS
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.09,0:01:52.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,用来控制各种程序分配的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.09,0:01:52.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,are in control and share time out to the programs.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.32,0:01:59.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,在AGC里 程序运行的时间是由其重要程度来决定的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.32,0:01:59.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,In the AGC, the programs controlled how much time they got depending on how important they were.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:59.72,0:02:01.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如在紧急情况下
Dialogue: 2,0:01:59.72,0:02:01.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,So in the case of an emergency,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.63,0:02:05.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,最高优先级的程序就会得到最多的运行时间
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.63,0:02:05.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,the highest priority programs would get most amount of the time,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.31,0:02:09.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,其他无关操作就会被搁置来释放资源
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.31,0:02:09.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,and non-essential operations were dropped to free up resources,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.12,0:02:15.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个理念成为了之后许多载人任务系统中的关键
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.12,0:02:15.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,which became the basis of mission critical system for all manned mission afterwards.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.12,0:02:21.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,AGC的性能和第一代PC差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.12,0:02:21.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,The computer had a performance somewhere around that of the first generation of personal computers,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.34,0:02:25.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,像Apple II, commodore 64, ZX Spectrum之类
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.34,0:02:25.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,like the Apple II, commodore 64, ZX Spectrum,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.06,0:02:30.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,但它们都是70年代末才出现的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.06,0:02:30.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,which would arrive 10 years later in the late 70’s.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.59,0:02:37.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,AGC有2k的RAM、36K的ROM
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.59,0:02:37.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,It had 2k of RAM and 36k of fixed storage rope core memory or ROM,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.20,0:02:42.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,全部纯手工打造 要花费几个月时间
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.20,0:02:42.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this was woven by hand and took months to assemble,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.30,0:02:46.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以就连系统Bug也是真的被"编"进去的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.30,0:02:46.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,so any software bugs were literally woven into the system.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.04,0:02:51.61,辉中,,0,0,0,,用AGC和现在iPhone 6做对比
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.04,0:02:51.61,辉英,,0,0,0,,A comparison between the Apollo Guidance Computer and say an iPhone 6
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.76,0:02:55.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,有点不严谨 因为AGC不属于通用计算机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.76,0:02:55.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,is tricky because the AGC was not a general purpose computer.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:55.88,0:03:00.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,它是用来做非常特殊的任务的 拥有独一无二的操作系统
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.88,0:03:00.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was built for a very specific task, had a unique operating system.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.80,0:03:04.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且中间还差48年的科技进步
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.80,0:03:04.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,That and also the 48-year gap in the technologies used,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.24,0:03:09.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以我们只能非常粗略的估计它们之间性能差异
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.24,0:03:09.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,mean we can only really get very rough estimates on the differency performance.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.68,0:03:13.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,苹果iPhone 6搭载ARM A8处理器
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.68,0:03:13.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Apple iPhone 6 has the ARM A8 processor,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.48,0:03:19.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,有16亿晶体管 AGC有12300个
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.48,0:03:19.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,which has about 1.6 billion transistors in it, the AGC had just 12,300.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.04,0:03:26.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,iPhone 6有1G的RAM 是AGC的488000倍
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.04,0:03:26.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,This iPhone 6 has 1Gb of RAM, about 488,000 times the AGC,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.35,0:03:34.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,128G的ROM 大概是AGC的350万倍
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.35,0:03:34.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this one, 128Gb of non-volatile storage or about 3.5 million times the AGC.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.73,0:03:43.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,至于性能 iPhone 6大概是AGC的400万到3000万倍
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.73,0:03:39.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,As for performance, the iPhone 6 is maybe somewhere
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.18,0:03:43.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,between 4 and 30 Million times faster than the AGC,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.24,0:03:45.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,这要看是做什么类型的计算
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.24,0:03:45.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,depending upon what type of calculations are being done.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.19,0:03:49.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,要是算上iPhone的GPU，那就更多了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.19,0:03:49.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,And if you include the iPhone’s GPU it would be even more.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.22,0:03:54.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以如果你在阿波罗飞船上要登月了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.22,0:03:54.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,So, if you had to fly back to the moon in an Apollo craft and given the choice,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.83,0:03:59.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,你会把你性命托付给几个iPhone还是AGC？
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.83,0:03:59.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,would you trust your life to a couple of iPhones in place of the AGC’s?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.52,0:04:03.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,别忘了你们用来上B站给UP三连的智能手机运算能力可是比
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.52,0:04:03.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because you would actually have more computing power in just one of these
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.00,0:04:07.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,当年阿波罗任务中全NASA拥有的计算机总和都高到不知道哪里去
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.00,0:04:07.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,than the whole of NASA had during all the Apollo missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.80,0:04:11.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,但万一你的iPhone死机 那你就完蛋了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.80,0:04:11.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, if your iPhone crashed you would be in big trouble,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.68,0:04:15.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为AGC虽然古老 但它是专门设计可以从死机、过载等情况恢复过来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.68,0:04:15.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,whereas the ancient AGC was designed to recover from crashes or overloads,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.80,0:04:20.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,自动继续运行 说白了 它不怕死机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.80,0:04:20.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,and continue by itself, in essence, it was designed to be crash proof,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.96,0:04:24.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,在任务的一些关键时刻这是非常重要的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.96,0:04:24.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,something that is needed in mission critical situations.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.96,0:04:28.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,对比两种计算机啊 当然要看性能 但也要考虑使用的情境
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.96,0:04:28.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,The problem we have here is the context in which we see the Apollo computer today.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.37,0:04:33.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,今天我们身边有那么多性能强劲的计算机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.37,0:04:33.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,We are now surrounded by computers, hugely more powerful,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.50,0:04:35.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们却以为那是理所当然的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.50,0:04:35.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we don’t give them a second thought.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.90,0:04:39.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在当时那个年代 对于一个不是计算机工程师
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.90,0:04:39.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,It’s very difficult for most people who are not computer engineers
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.13,0:04:43.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者不是汇编语言程序员来说 用那么少的资源做这件事
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.13,0:04:43.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,or assembler language programmers to imagine how you could do anything
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.10,0:04:45.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,难度超乎想象
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.10,0:04:45.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,with such limited resources.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.60,0:04:49.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,别忘了这东西是1962年设计出来的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.60,0:04:49.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,What we forget is that at the time of the design in 1962,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.02,0:04:51.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以说是世界上第一台嵌入式计算机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.02,0:04:51.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,this was to be the first embedded computer.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.01,0:04:55.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,简直是小型计算机的一大步
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.01,0:04:55.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was huge leap forward in miniaturised computing.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.34,0:04:59.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,计算机突然从房子那么大变成公文包那么大
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.34,0:04:59.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,From something the size of a large room to the size of a briefcase.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.93,0:05:03.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,这也是软件编程技术的大跃进
Dialogue: 2,0:04:59.93,0:05:03.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would also be giant leap forward for software programming,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.44,0:05:07.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,软件第一次用来实时处理问题
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.44,0:05:07.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,and the first time that software would be used for real-time problem solving,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.88,0:05:12.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,这是整个任务的关键 没有它不一定会死多少人
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.88,0:05:12.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,that would be key to the entire mission, if it failed then people could die.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.86,0:05:14.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,但它的研发难度简直了都
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.86,0:05:14.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,But its development was far from easy.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.04,0:05:19.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,据说如果最开始研发人员预测到了1961年他们将要面对的难题
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.04,0:05:19.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,It’s said that if the designers had known then in 1961 what they learned later,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.56,0:05:22.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者对合同让他们造什么有个清楚的了解
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.56,0:05:22.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,or had a complete specification when given the contract to make it,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.29,0:05:24.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们肯定会认为这件事
Dialogue: 2,0:05:23.29,0:05:24.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,they would have most likely concluded
Dialogue: 1,0:05:24.91,0:05:29.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,在当时 以60年代的科技水平是完全不可能的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.91,0:05:29.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,that it was just not have been possible with early 1960s technology.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.40,0:05:42.24,辉注,,0,0,0,,很高兴通知您NASA今日宣布指派MIT的设备实验室\N研发阿波罗飞船项目中的制导与导航系统。阿波罗飞\N船可以搭载三名宇航员往返月球。{\u1}MIT是阿波罗项目\N选中的第一个团队{\u0}，总承包商的竞标正在进行。另外，\NMIT的设备实验室还要负责开发阿波罗任务的地面支持\N与检查设备。合同包含第一年大约四百万美元的费用。
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.60,0:05:34.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,阿波罗制导与导航系统和软件的设计研发合同
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.60,0:05:34.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,The contract of the design development construction of the Apollo guidance navigation systems and software
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.13,0:05:40.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,在1961年8月签给了麻省理工学院
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.13,0:05:40.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,was given to the MIT in August 1961,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.08,0:05:44.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,而没有给NASA的老客户IBM
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.08,0:05:44.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,instead of NASA's normal computer contractors IBM.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.07,0:05:48.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,合同里说的并不详细
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.07,0:05:48.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,But there was no specifications given in the contract,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.44,0:05:55.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为在阿波罗项目早期 连NASA里也没人能说清这"阿波罗计算机"到底要干嘛
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.44,0:05:51.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,because no one in NASA really knew
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.16,0:05:55.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,what the requirement of an Apollo computer would be at that early stage.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.47,0:05:58.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,而在60年代整整十年里
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.47,0:05:58.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,As the project developed throughout the 1960s,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.05,0:06:02.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,这项工程的巨大难度才慢慢浮出水面 远远超乎最开始人们的想象
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.05,0:06:02.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,it became apparent that the task was going to be much more difficult than they first considered.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.00,0:06:12.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,60年代中后期 计算机的研发问题已经关乎到 整个阿波罗计划的生死存亡了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.00,0:06:04.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,By the mid to late 60s,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.80,0:06:08.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,the problems in the computers' development were in danger of sinking
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.11,0:06:12.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,be entire of Apollo program if they couldn't get the AGC to work.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.15,0:06:17.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,1966年 在命运多舛的阿波罗1号测试中
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.15,0:06:17.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,By the time of testing in 1966 for the ill-fated Apollo 1,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.53,0:06:25.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,人们发现AGC软件里的Bug会导致导航路径不可靠
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.53,0:06:21.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,it became apparent that bugs in the software meant that the AGC
Dialogue: 2,0:06:21.15,0:06:25.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,couldnot be relied upon to do the navigational course calculations
Dialogue: 1,0:06:25.69,0:06:27.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,说白了它算不准
Dialogue: 2,0:06:25.69,0:06:27.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,as it was just not accurate enough.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.22,0:06:32.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,搞不好飞船返回的时候就进错轨道了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.22,0:06:32.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,Something that could put the craft into the wrong orbit when it returned to earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:33.37,0:06:38.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,最开始决定在地面用IBM的大型计算机做轨道计算
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.37,0:06:38.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was decided that IBM mainframe computers on the ground would do the course calculations
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.57,0:06:41.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后把数据发送到指令舱的AGC上去执行
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.57,0:06:41.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,and send them to the AGC in the command module to be implemented.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.28,0:06:50.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,这种方法可以把问题都在地面上用更强大的计算机解决再传回AGC
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.28,0:06:45.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,This way round, known limitations could be worked around
Dialogue: 2,0:06:45.64,0:06:50.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,with much more powerful ground based computers and the results then sent to the AGCs.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.36,0:06:56.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,但指令舱必须有自行计算的能力
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.36,0:06:56.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, the command module had to be capable of working independently,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.56,0:07:00.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,防止与地面的通讯失效 比如飞到月球背面
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.56,0:07:00.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,if the ground link was broken like when it was flying behind the moon,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.22,0:07:02.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者有其他信号干扰的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.22,0:07:02.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,or if someone tried to jam the signal.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.84,0:07:08.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以利用惯性制导系统 与观察星位结合的方法定位
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.84,0:07:05.68,辉英,,0,0,0,,So using a combination of the inertial guidance system
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.68,0:07:08.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,and built in Sextant to check the star positions,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.49,0:07:12.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,计算机仍然能在无需地面链接的情况下进行导航
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.49,0:07:12.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,they could still navigate without a ground-linked data.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.44,0:07:19.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,至于登月舱 信号发到地球再传回月球各会有一秒半的延迟
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.44,0:07:16.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,As for the lander, the round trip delay of 1.5 seconds
Dialogue: 2,0:07:16.19,0:07:19.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,for the signals to get to the moon and back to earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:19.00,0:07:23.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个延迟对于下降段着陆控制来说实在是太大了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:19.00,0:07:23.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,would have been too long for ground control to remotely land the descent stage,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.69,0:07:26.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为各种反馈必须实时处理
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.69,0:07:26.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,because the feedback needed to be in real time.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.68,0:07:33.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,最后 下降级AGC要和着陆雷达、宇航员共同合作才能在月球着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.68,0:07:29.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,To this end, the descent stage AGC
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.56,0:07:33.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,would work with the landing radar and the astronauts to land on the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:33.80,0:07:37.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,这让阿波罗11号任务在最后阶段差点取消
Dialogue: 2,0:07:33.80,0:07:37.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,This led to the Apollo 11 landing almost being aborted
Dialogue: 1,0:07:37.56,0:07:39.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,当时着陆雷达里有个Bug
Dialogue: 2,0:07:37.56,0:07:39.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,when a design bug in the landing radar,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:39.95,0:07:44.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,登月舱下降的时候为了防止紧急终止 着陆雷达被设成待命状态
Dialogue: 2,0:07:39.95,0:07:44.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,which had been left on standby during the descent in case of an emergency abort,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.86,0:07:48.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,制造了一堆信号导致AGC计算机过载
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.86,0:07:48.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,created a flood of signals that overloaded the AGC,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:48.59,0:07:53.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,在着陆前触发了计算机代码错误警告
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.59,0:07:53.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,and setting off computer error code alarms just before the landing.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.96,0:08:00.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于AGC的设计 不像我们心中 iPhone或者普通的电脑会崩溃或者锁定
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.96,0:07:57.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Due to the AGC’s design, instead of crashing or locking up
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.44,0:08:00.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,like we maybe expect our iPhone or normal computer to do,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.52,0:08:05.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,它在重启前会把最重要的任务以外的都舍弃
Dialogue: 2,0:08:00.52,0:08:05.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,it dropped all but the most important tasks before then restarting itself.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:05.48,0:08:08.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,这不是它的缺陷 这叫重置保护
Dialogue: 2,0:08:05.48,0:08:08.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,This was not a fault, it was called RESET Protection.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.18,0:08:13.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,AGC的设计会让它保存所有目前运算的数据
Dialogue: 2,0:08:09.18,0:08:13.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,The AGC was designed so that all of the current data it was working on was stored.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.90,0:08:18.11,辉中,,0,0,0,,使它能在任何时候关闭、再打开或者重置
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.90,0:08:18.11,辉英,,0,0,0,,This meant that it could be turned off and on again or reset at any time,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:18.19,0:08:21.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,之后它会从之前的地方继续运算
Dialogue: 2,0:08:18.19,0:08:21.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,and it would just continue to work from where it left off.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.79,0:08:25.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,有点像PC的睡眠模式再开机
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.79,0:08:25.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,A bit like when your PC goes into sleep mode and then come back again,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:26.09,0:08:28.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,但比这快多了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:26.09,0:08:28.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,but much, much quicker.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:29.07,0:08:31.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些特性让阿波罗11号任务最后没有终止
Dialogue: 2,0:08:29.07,0:08:31.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,These features saved the mission from aborting
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.63,0:08:34.73,辉中,,0,0,0,,而是让阿姆斯特朗接手控制了登月舱的航向
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.63,0:08:34.73,辉英,,0,0,0,,and allowed Armstrong to control the orientation of the lander
Dialogue: 1,0:08:34.73,0:08:38.43,辉中,,0,0,0,,同时AGC控制登月舱的下降 最后成功着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:08:34.73,0:08:38.43,辉英,,0,0,0,,whilst the AGC controlled the descent to a successful landing.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:38.92,0:08:44.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,说白了在阿波罗计划里 人类用性能堪比如今烤面包机芯片的计算机
Dialogue: 2,0:08:38.92,0:08:44.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Its things like this that made what is now about as powerful as the microcontroller
Dialogue: 1,0:08:44.19,0:08:49.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,把人安全的送上月球并返回 整整六次
Dialogue: 2,0:08:44.19,0:08:49.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,in a toaster get men to the moon and safely back again, 6 times.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:49.90,0:08:54.24,辉中,,0,0,0,,它不但为之后的太空探索提供了范例
Dialogue: 2,0:08:49.90,0:08:54.24,辉英,,0,0,0,,It also created a paradigm shift not only in space exploration,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.41,0:08:56.49,辉中,,0,0,0,,也促进了之后计算机的发展
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.41,0:08:56.49,辉英,,0,0,0,,but also computing for the future.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.88,0:09:03.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,最后感谢观看
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.88,0:09:03.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,And as always, thanks for watching, and please subscribe, rate, and share.
